==English==
===Pronunciation===
*krĭb, /krɪb/, /<tt>krIb</tt>/
*:[[Rhymes:English:-ɪb|Rhymes: -ɪb]]

===Noun===
[[Category:English nouns]]
'''crib''' (''plural:'' '''cribs''')

# A baby's [[cot]] with [[high]] [[side]]s.
# A feeding [[trough]] for [[animal]]s.
# A [[bin]] or [[box]] for storing [[grain]].
# A [[Nativity]] [[scene]] consisting of [[statue]]s of [[Mary]], [[Joseph]] and [[Jesus]], and various other characters such as the [[Three Wise Men]].
#(''[[cryptanalysis]]'') A known piece of [[information]] [[corresponding]] to a section of [[encrypted]] text, that is then used to work out the remaining sections.<!--This is not an example of the usage of the word:
Eg, during [[WW2]], British [[cryptanalysts]] knew that many [[German]] messages contained the term "Heil Hitler", and were able to use this [[pattern]] to help work out the day's [[encryption]] codes.-->
#[[Petty]] [[theft]] or [[plagiarism]].
#[[notes|Notes]] to refer to, rather than speaking or writing ad lib.
#Short for the [[card game]] [[cribbage]].
#In the card game cribbage, the cards [[discard]]ed by [[player]]s and used by the [[dealer]].

